  "texts": [
    "end order of an inner psychological economy made up of belief-and desire-like entities meets the causal order of the environment.",
    "As we've seen, in the good case, the structure of the latter order is an inverse of the former.",
    "The environmental causal pathway follows a plan set out in advance by the agent who acts: given an end, she intends the means; and the means, once taken, is the cause of that end being fulfilled.",
    "Assuming this model, it has been widely thought that some actions must be basicthat is, there must be things an agent does that are not ends that other actions are the means to but themselves directly the means that the agent takes to set everything else in motion.",
    "Such actions are the fundamental interface between agent and world."
  ]
